# [\#3413 Issue](https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/issues/3413) `closed`: Very long string literals are placed after the metadata hash
**Labels**: `bug :bug:`


#### <img src="https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/20340?v=4" width="50">[axic](https://github.com/axic) opened issue at [2018-01-20 12:26](https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/issues/3413):

```
 pragma solidity ^0.4.18;
contract test{
    string f = 'abcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabc';
    string g = 'abcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabcabc';
    string data = 'blah';
    function get() public view returns (string){
        return data;
    }

}
```

will produce the following bytecode:

```

```

Note that the long string literal is after the metadata hash.

`a165627a7a72305820669decc05d9cee87e8196f2f52c21b210b191dbabc75ef37a23055659e4459bf`

`0029`

`616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263616263`

This is due to the special `PushString` type in assembly.

(From https://github.com/ethereum/remix/issues/604)


#### <img src="https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/9073706?v=4" width="50">[chriseth](https://github.com/chriseth) commented at [2018-01-20 12:26](https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/issues/3413#issuecomment-372697070):

This is not a bug: The metadata is at the end of the runtime bytecode, not at the end of the creation time bytecode:
```
> solc --bin-runtime /tmp/x.sol
Warning: This is a pre-release compiler version, please do not use it in production.

======= /tmp/x.sol:test =======
Binary of the runtime part: 

```
